cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.SD

This paper combines natural language processing and machine learning to train a classification model for Integrative Complexity (IC) in text. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also deals with social media analytics, which suggests the sub-category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The use of machine learning also points towards cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with large-scale data analysis, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
